      <h2>Overview</h2>

      <p>The Traveling Times is a personal creative journal. We respect your privacy and have built this site to work without collecting your personal information. This policy explains exactly what data (if any) is involved when you visit.</p>

      <h2>What We Don't Do</h2>

      <ul>
        <li>We do not require accounts or logins.</li>
        <li>We do not run advertisements.</li>
        <li>We do not use tracking cookies.</li>
        <li>We do not use analytics pixels or tracking scripts.</li>
        <li>We do not collect, store, or sell personal data.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Local Storage</h2>

      <p>Some features save preferences in your browser using <code>localStorage</code>. This data stays entirely on your device and is never transmitted to us or anyone else. You can clear it at any time through your browser settings.</p>

      <p>Here is what we store and why:</p>

      <ul>
        <li><code>ttt-theme</code> — Remembers your dark/light mode preference.</li>
        <li><code>ttt-reading-list</code> — Saves articles you bookmark to your reading list.</li>
        <li><code>ttt-rs-font-size</code> — Stores your preferred reading font size.</li>
        <li><code>ttt-rs-font</code> — Stores your preferred reading font family.</li>
        <li><code>ttt-focus</code> — Remembers whether you have focus mode enabled.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Newsletter</h2>

      <p>If you choose to subscribe to our newsletter, your email address is sent to <a href="https://buttondown.com" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Buttondown</a>, our newsletter service. Buttondown stores your email address for the sole purpose of sending you new articles when they are published. You can unsubscribe at any time using the link in every email. Buttondown's own <a href="https://buttondown.com/legal/privacy" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">privacy policy</a> applies to newsletter data.</p>

      <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>

      <h3>Cloudflare Pages</h3>
      <p>This site is hosted on <a href="https://pages.cloudflare.com" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Cloudflare Pages</a>. Cloudflare may collect basic server logs (IP addresses, page requests) for security and performance purposes. Cloudflare does not place tracking cookies on this site.</p>

      <h3>Bunny Fonts</h3>
      <p>Fonts are loaded from <a href="https://fonts.bunny.net" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Bunny Fonts</a>, a GDPR-compliant, privacy-friendly font CDN. Bunny Fonts does not track users or collect personal data.</p>

      <h3>Pagefind</h3>
      <p>The site search is powered by <a href="https://pagefind.app" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Pagefind</a>, which runs entirely in your browser. No search queries or data are sent to any external server.</p>

      <h3>Service Worker</h3>
      <p>This site uses a service worker to cache pages for offline reading. All cached data stays on your device and is never transmitted elsewhere.</p>

      <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>

      <p>The Traveling Times is run by a young person, and we take privacy seriously. This site does not knowingly collect any personal information from children or anyone else. There are no account sign-ups, no forms that ask for personal details (beyond an optional email for the newsletter), and no tracking of any kind.</p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>

      <p>If you or a parent or guardian has any questions about this privacy policy, please email <a href="mailto:{{ site.email }}">{{ site.email }}</a>.</p>

      <p><em>Last updated: April 7, 2026</em></p>

